const faqs = [
  { q: 'How many times will the Anker PowerCore 10000 PD Redux charge a phone?', a: 'The 10000mAh capacity translates to roughly two full charges for an iPhone 15 (which has a 3349mAh battery) and about 1.8 charges for a Samsung Galaxy S24. Real-world capacity is lower than the label because of voltage conversion losses — expect about 6500mAh of usable output at the phone. For most users, that means one and a half to two full charges from empty to 100%.' },
  { q: 'Can the Anker PowerCore 10000 PD Redux charge a MacBook?', a: 'It can charge a MacBook Air or MacBook Pro, but only slowly and only when the laptop is asleep or idle. The 30W output is below the minimum most MacBooks draw while in use (45W for the MacBook Air, 67W for the Pro). In our test, the bank added about 10% to a MacBook Air over 30 minutes while the laptop was awake and in use. It is best treated as an emergency top-up for laptops, not a primary charger.' },
  { q: 'How long does it take to recharge the PowerCore 10000 PD Redux?', a: 'With a 30W USB-C charger (not included), the bank recharges from empty to full in about 3.5 hours. With an 18W charger, it takes about 5 hours. With a standard 10W USB-A charger, expect about 7 hours. The bank supports USB-C Power Delivery input, so the faster your charger, the faster it recharges. The included USB-C to USB-C cable supports up to 60W, so you are not limited by the cable.' },
